16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 There is hereby appropriated to the Legislative Service Bureau
20 from monies not otherwise appropriated from the ARPA Administrative
21 Costs Fund created in Section 255.5 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma
22 Statutes, the sum of Thirty-four Thousand Six Hundred Ninety-two
23 Dollars ($34,692.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to pay
24
Req. No. 17530 Page 1

1 obli gations that may arise out of contracts during Fiscal Year 2027
2 related to the American Rescue Plan Act of 2021.
3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
4 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
5 There is hereby appropriated to the Legislative Service Bureau
6 from monies not otherwise appropriated from the Statewide Recovery
7 Fund found in Section 255 of the Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
8 the sum of Two Hundred Thirteen Thousand Three Hundred Eight Dollars
9 ($213,308.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to pay
10 obligations that may arise out of contracts during Fiscal Year 2027
11 related to the American Rescue Plan Act of 2021.
12 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
13 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
14 There is hereby appropriated to the Office of Management and
15 Enterprise Services from monies not otherwise appropriated from the
16 ARPA Administrative Costs Fund created in Section 255.5 of Title 62
17 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum of Eight Hundred Six Thousand
18 Sixty Dollars ($806,060.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary
19 to pay for expenses arising from implementing programs and
20 expenditures in accordance with actions taken by the Joint Committee
21 on Pandemic Relief Funding.
22 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
23 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 17530 Page 2

1 There is hereby appropriated to the Office of Management and
2 Enterprise Services from monies not otherwise appropriated from the
3 Statewide Recovery Fund found in Section 255 of the Title 68 of the
4 Oklahoma Statutes, the sum of One Million Six Hundred Twelve
5 Thousand One Hundred Twenty Dollars ($1,612,120.00) or so much
6 thereof as may be necessary to pay for expenses arising from
7 implementing programs and expenditures in accordance with actions
8 taken by the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding.
9 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
10 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
11 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
12 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
